item.title: 【Singles (lossless)】Travis Scott, Bad Bunny & The Weeknd - K-POP | Qobuz Hi-Res 24-bit 88.2 kHz
item.description:
Genre: Electronic, Latin
Released: Jul 21, 2023

"K-POP" is a song by American rapper Travis Scott, Puerto Rican rapper Bad Bunny and Canadian singer the Weeknd, released on July 21, 2023, through Epic and Cactus Jack Records as the lead single from Scott's upcoming fourth studio album Utopia. It is Scott's first single as the primary artist since 2021's simultaneously released singles "Escape Plan" and "Mafia".

Scott announced the collaboration on his social media accounts on July 19, 2023. Both Bad Bunny and the Weeknd had previously been among artists named to appear on Utopia, with Scott previewing an unreleased song featuring Bad Bunny at a club in Monaco in May 2023. Bad Bunny said in an interview with Rolling Stone in its July/August 2023 issue that he and Scott "worked on that a while back".
